<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="42" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="42">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="42">
This species and 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. intrusus" pageId="23" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="intrusus">X. intrusus</taxonomicName>
are common in pines. It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. intrusus" pageId="23" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="intrusus">X. intrusus</taxonomicName>
by the larger, shallow strial punctures and the smaller declivital denticles.
</paragraph>
